r he’s like a firstborn bull,"},{"type":"poetry","content":"He’ll gore the nations with those horns,"},{"type":"poetry","content":"Ephraim by the ten thousands will do this,"}],[{"type":"prose","content":"Zebulun and Issachar:"},{"type":"poetry","content":"“Celebrate, Zebulun, as you go out,"},{"type":"poetry","content":"They’ll invite people to the Mountain"},{"type":"poetry","content":"For they will have hauled riches in from the sea"}],[{"type":"prose","content":"Gad:"},{"type":"poetry","content":"“Blessed is he who makes Gad large."},{"type":"poetry","content":"He took one look and grabbed the best place for himself,"},{"type":"poetry","content":"He took his place at the head,"}],[{"type":"prose","content":"Dan:"},{"type":"poetry","content":"“Dan is a lion’s cub"}],[{"type":"prose","content":"Naphtali:"},{"type":"poetry","content":"“Naphtali brims with blessings,"},{"type":"poetry","content":"As he takes possession"}],[{"type":"prose","content":"Asher:"},{"type":"poetry","content":"“Asher, best blessed of the sons!"},{"type":"poetry","content":"Safe behind iron-clad doors and gates,"},{"type":"prose","content":"* * *"}],[{"type":"poetry","content":"There is none like God, Jeshurun,"},{"type":"poetry","content":"The ancient God is home"},{"type":"poetry","content":"He drove out the enemy before you"},{"type":"poetry","content":"Israel lived securely,"},{"type":"poetry","content":"In grain and wine country"}]]